# Reuse Before Create

Before adding a component, hook, utility, or helper, **search this project first**. Extend or reuse what exists — do not copy patterns from `manda-app/`.

## Required workflow

1. **Search** — grep or semantic search under `src/features/`, `src/shared/`, `src/app/`.
2. **Reuse** — import from feature barrels (`features/auth/index.ts`) or `shared/ui/`.
3. **Extract** — if the same logic appears twice, extract to `shared/` or the owning feature's `api/` / `hooks/`.
4. **Create new** — only when nothing suitable exists.

## Where to look

| Need                              | Check first                                                                                           |
| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Staff auth / session              | `features/auth/` — `useAuth`, guards, `staff-auth.ts`, `staff-storage.ts`                             |
| App chrome (sidebar, shell)       | `features/shell/components/` — `Sidebar`, `Topbar`, `AppShell`                                        |
| Transactions (ops)                | `features/transactions/` — list/detail pages, `api/transactions.ts`                                   |
| Destructive ops confirmation      | `shared/ui/confirm-danger-dialog.tsx`                                                                 |
| UI atoms (buttons, fields, brand) | `shared/ui/` — `PrimaryButton`, `TextField`, `Avatar`, `MandaGlyph`, `MandaWordmark`, `LoadingScreen` |
| HTTP / errors                     | `shared/api/client.ts`, `shared/api/api-error.ts`                                                     |
| API types (staff OpenAPI)         | `shared/api/generated/` — regenerate with `npm run api:types`                                         |
| Design tokens                     | `src/app/global.css` (`--manda-*`)                                                                    |
| Route wiring                      | `app/router.tsx`, `app/App.tsx`                                                                       |
| Query defaults                    | `app/query-client.ts`                                                                                 |
| Electron / tokens                 | `electron/main.ts`, `electron/preload.ts` — don't duplicate IPC in renderer                           |
| Visual reference (backoffice)     | `tmp/manda/screens-backoffice.jsx` only                                                               |

**Not backoffice references:** `tmp/manda/screens-auth.jsx`, `screens-chat.jsx`, etc. are mobile prototypes — see `manda-app/` for those.

## Feature layout

New domain work goes in **`features/<name>/`**:

```
features/kyc/
├── api/
├── components/
├── pages/
└── index.ts          # optional public exports
```

Do **not** import another feature's internal files — use its barrel or move shared code to `shared/`.

## Styling

- Co-located **`*.module.css`** — no inline `style={{ … }}` for layout/theme.
- Use `--manda-*` from `global.css` before new hex values.
- Reuse `shared/ui/` before one-off styled elements.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — duplicate confirm modal
{
  open && <div className="overlay">...</div>;
}

// ✅ GOOD
import { ConfirmDangerDialog } from "@/shared/ui/confirm-danger-dialog";
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw axios in a page
await axios.post(`/staff/transactions/${id}/confirm-escrow`);

// ✅ GOOD
import { confirmTransactionEscrow } from "@/features/transactions/api/transactions";
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — manda-app pattern
import { useAuth } from "@/providers/auth-provider";
import * as SecureStore from "expo-secure-store";

// ✅ GOOD — backoffice
import { useAuth } from "@/features/auth";
import { staffStorage } from "@/features/auth/storage/staff-storage";
```

## When generalizing

- Prefer one flexible component over near-identical copies.
- After extracting to `shared/ui/`, delete inlined duplicates.
